I’m a 19 year old white male, 120 pounds, 5’8, with congenital heart disease and depression. No medications.

So I’m going to be honest upfront and say that I’m beginning to think I may have some form of undiagnosed health anxiety or OCD. Please forgive me if these concerns are ridiculous or unfounded. Basically yesterday I accompanied a family member into a CT room while they were having a scan done. I was told this was okay and that I should just stand behind a mobile lead glass barrier in the corner of the room. The results didn’t show any issues but now all I can think about is the amount of radiation I exposed myself to while in the room. I’m worried it may have damaged or destroyed brain cells, and increased my risk of cancer. I can tell even reading this now how dumb it all sounds but I can’t help it.
